<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880415-0046 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Datacopy Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> DCPY </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Datacopy Corp. said it's holding talks with another company, which it didn't identify, regarding a possible acquisition of Datacopy for $6 a share.    Noting &quot;substantial unresolved issues&quot; in the talks, however, the maker of computer-imaging systems for personal computers used in specialized publishing warned there is &quot;no assurance&quot; the potential acquisition will be completed. In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Datacopy shares closed at $5.375, up 12.5 cents.    Company officials weren't available for comment. Datacopy, of Mountain View, Calif., has about 4.8 million common and common-equivalent shares outstanding, giving the proposed transaction an indicated value of about $28.7 million. </TEXT></DOC>